cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA) in the video domain, which involves spatio-temporal reasoning from videos to answer questions correctly. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) for understanding questions and answers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset and a new approach for VQA, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia content, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
